OL,3,C'We should have acted faster on Letby'
OL,4,Csays new head of nursing watchdog
OL,6,FShe continued to work in the Countess
OL,7,Fof Chester's risk and patient safety
OL,8,Fdepartment until her arrest in July
OL,9,F2018.
OL,11,FAfter her arrest, a senior lawyer at
OL,12,Fthe NMC concluded there was
OL,13,Finsufficient grounds to obtain an
OL,14,Finterim order ` which could have led
OL,15,Fto a suspension or restriction of
OL,16,Fpractice ` without her being charged.
OL,18,FOnce convicted, Letby was stripped of
OL,19,Fher nursing credentials and struck off
OL,20,Fthe register at an NMC fitness to
OL,21,Fpractise hearing in December 2023.
